    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by three elite-tier plays, led by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84), who draws a favorable matchup against Brayan Bello. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a strong BvP profile and a prime #3 spot in the order, pushing his score well into the elite range. Joining him at the top are **Kyle Tucker** (73.39) and **Gunnar Henderson** (73.38). **Gunnar Henderson** is particularly well-positioned today; despite a tricky matchup, the significant park factors and his role as the table-setter in the #1 spot make him a must-start. **Josh Lowe** (71.68) also warrants attention as a high-upside play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Fedde and a favorable 93% stolen base success rate against the opposing pitcher\u2019s delivery, which aligns perfectly with our organizational focus on elite speed.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Josh Jung** (52.80), who fell just shy of cracking the starting rotation. While **Josh Jung** offers a solid floor, the optimizer prioritized the higher ceiling of **Luis Robert Jr.** and the platoon-adjusted value of **Miguel Vargas**. We are closely monitoring the weather and lineup statuses for several players, particularly the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Liam Hicks**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill**. Should any of these players drop lower in their respective batting orders than the projected slots, their efficiency scores will need to be re-evaluated. We are also wary of **Heliot Ramos**, who remains sidelined not only due to a lower projected score but also due to a 40% rain risk, keeping him firmly on the bench for this slate.",
